Abia State Governor, Dr. Okezie Ikpeazu, has commended two members of the National Youth Service Corps (NYSC) serving in the state for their efforts at contributing to government’s fight against the coronavirus pandemic. The duo, Babatunde Dolapo Dayo and Sebe Godspower Oghenemaroh, fabricated and donated hands-free washing machines for sanitising and washing hands as support to the state in her fight against COVID -19. The governor, who pledged the sum of N500,000 as cash gift to the youth corps members also directed the Secretary to State Government (SSG) to make purchase of the machines in large quantity, which according to him, would be placed at strategic places for public use. Speaking during the presentation of the machines, Governor Ikpeazu, who was represented by the Secretary to the State Government, Barr Chris Ezem, applauded the ingenuity and hard work of the youth corps members and urged them to mass produce the machines to enable the government procure and deploy them to schools and government offices in the state. Dear valued readers, subscribe to the Daily Trust e-paper to continue enjoying our diet of authoritative news. Kindly subscribe here “While the global community is reeling from the negative socio-economic impacts of the novel COVID-19 pandemic, I see opportunities for those who are willing to think outside the box to solve problems. Our people in Abia have long taken advantage of the outbreak of the disease to produce high quality personal protective equipment (PPE), and as youth corps members serving in our state, you have keyed into the message and philosophy of our hard working people.” The machines which were fabricated with locally sourced materials ensure a healthier way of washing one’s hands as they are operated with the feet without having to touch the sanitiser, the liquid soap or even the tap for running water. Abia, Sokoto, 3 other states receive 11,002 corps members NYSC swears in 1900 corp members in Abia 1106 corps members to 